Russian Equity Movers: Aeroflot, Rosneft, Polymetal Are Active

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-05-06T16:00:48Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/russian-equity-movers-aeroflot-rosneft-polymetal-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  climbed 2.2
percent to 1,681.01 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, erasing an
earlier loss of as much as 1.4 percent. The dollar-denominated
RTS Index gained 1 percent to 1,936.29.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Aeroflot (AFLT RX),  Russia ’s biggest airline, gained
the most in almost six months after oil tumbled 8.6 percent
yesterday, the most in two years, with more than half of the
decline coming after the close of trading in Moscow yesterday.
The shares rallied 3.8 percent to 67.35 rubles.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX), the country’s largest oil producer
advanced 2.9 percent to 235.33 rubles, the first gain in five
days. BP Plc said a court panel gave permission for its share
swap with Rosneft to proceed on condition that TNK-BP be
assigned the accord to explore the Arctic.  OAO Polymetal (PMTL RX), a Russian silver producer,
retreated for the fourth day, losing 3.5 percent to 483.9 rubles
as silver futures declined.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason Corcoran in Moscow at 
